freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Nothing to do with COVID-19.  On Sunday, I had corneal abrasions (minor) from pollen in the air and went to urgent care. She prescribed an antibiotic for my eye and I feel great today.
Runny nose and tiredness, but I dont believe it is because of the vaccine. I was caught outside when the temperature dropped without a warm coat, and caught a chill.

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Cramping in lower extremities and dizziness. This all happened during the night. I am fine now except for the headache and tiredness.
